# ASCII Art Generator 🎨✨

## Introduction
This project demonstrates how a **single line of Python code** can generate **stunning ASCII art** using the `art` library. With this simple yet powerful script, you can convert text into artistic representations directly in your terminal! 🚀

## Features
✅ Convert text into ASCII art effortlessly  
✅ Perfect for personal branding, CLI projects, and fun coding experiments  
✅ Uses minimal code for **maximum creativity**  

## Installation
To use this project, you need to install the `art` module. Run the following command:
```bash
pip install art
```

## Usage
Run the following Python script:
```python
from art import text2art

print(text2art("I am Quratulain Shah"))
```
This will generate a **beautiful ASCII representation** of your text right in your terminal! 🎭

## Example Output
```
  _____                     _ _       _       _     
 |_   _|                   (_) |     (_)     | |    
   | |  _ __ ___   __ _ ___ _| |_ ___ _  __ _| |__  
